pr_body:
**Summary**
- Developed basic CI/CD pipeline for the OrcaAL repository.  Should fix #2 

**Major changes**
- Linting (flake8 with python scripts and eslint with typescript)
- Versioning, with an incremental patch every time a successful deployment is made to Docker Hub and GH Pages
- Deployment (to Docker Hub for API and ML endpoint, and GH Pages for web app) - this and versioning only run upon push to the master branch
- Scheduled periodic checks every 12 hours at 0530 and 1730 UTC (that the OrcaAL Github Pages site is up and running)

**Miscellaneous changes**
- Added requirements.txt for ML endpoint installation alternative, as pipenv installation method does not seem to work for WSL Ubuntu-18.04
- Replaced all .gitignore files in separate folders with a single .gitignore file in the root directory
- Modified documentation to contain more specific installation instructions
- Changed code (to check for presence of specific table in database) in the API folder for compatibility with newer versions of SQLAlchemy 1.4+ 
- Renamed model path in readme and .env file to correct model name

pr_body:
Resolves #12. Builds on #23 #24 #26 #27. This PR aims to incorporate a docker compose file for development. Additionally, while not within the scope of the branch name, a Github Action was implemented for running tests as well, as there were some changes made to the test docker compose file along the way, especially with regard to the networking aspect. 

Major changes:
- Docker compose file for development

Miscellaneous changes:
 - Github Action to automatically run tests with docker compose test

Actions required:
- Add secret `AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID` to OrcaAL repository secrets
- Add secret `AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY` to OrcaAL repository secrets

pr_body:
Resolves #16. Builds on #23 #24 #26 #27 #28. Applies linting and formatting based on a pre-commit configuration. Credit to @Molkree for providing the [base config template](https://github.com/orcasound/orca-action-workflow/blob/c7c28ed11a0d7556bf0aebbc60e3a125df28ab57/.pre-commit-config.yaml) from the Orca Action Workflow project. 

Major changes:
- Incorporation of setup.cfg to specify configurations, and a pre-commit yaml file to specify which tools to run.
- Added eslint on top of the existing python utilities to format the javascript and typescript code
- Any changes to other files as a result of linting and formatting
- Added GH Action for linting and formatting 

Minor changes:
- Moved .eslintrc.json file out of the webapp folder in order to be accessed by pre-commit for linting configurations
- Refactored the testing and linting+formatting into a single GH Action, to be run whenever new commits are pushed to a remote/PR.

pr_body:
Resolves #23. Builds upon #24 and #26. This PR implements a docker compose file for testing purposes, with as minimal changes to the code as possible. 

Major Changes:
- Docker compose file for starting the different services and tearing them down after the testing is complete
- Refactoring of docker files to allow for multi-stage docker builds, which preserves only one docker file for each service
- Creating a docker file for the web app service for cypress testing

Miscellaneous Changes:
- Changing the order of how pytests are run (under test_routes.py), to avoid what likely seems to be a database lock issue, see [here](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/64277512/pytest-marks-test-as-passed-after-an-assertion-error) for more details
- Changing some configurations in the webpack files to allow for external users to access the webapp when run within a Docker container

pr_body:
Resolves #12. Builds on #23 #24 #26 #27. This PR aims to incorporate a docker compose file for development. Additionally, while not within the scope of the branch name, a Github Action was implemented for running tests as well, as there were some changes made to the test docker compose file along the way, especially with regard to the networking aspect. 

Major changes:
- Docker compose file for development

Miscellaneous changes:
 - Github Action to automatically run tests with docker compose test

Actions required:
- Add secret `AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID` to OrcaAL repository secrets
- Add secret `AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY` to OrcaAL repository secrets
